# Evidence Synthesis

## Inputs
- documentation excerpts
- diagnostic findings
- prior cases
- specialist agent responses

## Procedure
1. Identify the strongest evidence first
2. Separate confirmed facts from likely inferences
3. Resolve or explain conflicts between inputs
4. Present the most likely cause first
5. End with concrete next steps

## Rules
- Do not flatten uncertainty
- Cite or name the source of each major conclusion when possible
- Prefer primary evidence over memory or anecdote
